<a class='reflink' href='../1.gis/1.2.is.html#orderinversesemigroup'>natural order</a>

<div class='toload'>
<p>
We define a partial order on an inverse semigroup $S$ with any of the following equivalent statements
<div class="equation">\begin{align*}
s\leq t&\iff\exists e\in E(S)\left(te=s\right)\iff\exists e\in E(S)(et=s)\\
&\iff s=ts^*s\iff s=ss^*t
\end{align*}</div>
(the equivalence of these statements can be proven using Theorem <span class='ref' data-tag='theoreminverseiffescommute'></span>).
</p>
</div>